Title: Music for Millions

reviewText: The premise of this film is a great wartime story. The half is lovely, but unless you LOVE pianists, Jose Iturbi's solo performances really wear thin, each number seemingly longer than the last. Iturbi plays his way through the entire film and June Allyson isn't utilised enough. Still a nice film, not one to watch over and over though..
Title: Music for Millions

reviewText: A nice film with a lot of good music in it.  The acting was ok considering the story line and the main characters involved.  The studio was attempting to use Margaret as a Shirley Temple copy but did not have the cuteness or talent to compete, however it was a nice movie either way.

Title: Music for Millions

reviewText: is it a drama, or comedy, or musical that fhighlights the classics?  Yes to all three. June Allyson is part of a Orchestra that travels and plays for our servicemen during WWII. Margaret O'Brien plays her young sister who pays a visit. Without spoiling this film, it's one of the best films I have, made in 1944, and O'brien went on to win a special Oscar that year for this and two other films she made. The Delightfull Jimmy Durante and Jose Iturbi round out the players that makes it a unique film to own.
Title: Music for Millions
